Pre-Game Insights: The Utah Jazz will host the San Antonio Spurs for an NBA match on Friday, November 1, 2024.
Both franchises are motivated to win the game.
The Utah Jazz have not won a single game this season and have suffered three consecutive defeats.
San Antonio Spurs are aiming for the playoffs but faced a disappointing loss against the Oklahoma City Thunder.
Lauri Markkanen of the Utah Jazz is uncertain to play due to a lower back injury.
Jordan Clarkson may take over for Lauri Markkanen if he is unable to play.
The probable starting five for Utah Jazz includes Collin Sexton, Kayonte George, Taylor Hendricks, Lauri Markkanen, and Walker Kessler.
The probable starting five for San Antonio Spurs includes Chris Paul, Julian Champagnie, Harrison Barnes, Jeremy Sochan, and Victor Wembanyama.
Devin Vassell and Tre Jones will not play for the Spurs.
San Antonio Spurs are in a back-to-back situation after their loss to the Thunder.
